<!-- CHICAGO-SPECIFIC -->
<h2 id="chicago">Chicago-Specific Questions</h2>
<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How do Chicago winters affect vehicle wraps?</h3>
<p>Chicago's freeze-thaw cycles and road salt are tough on low-quality vinyl. Cast vinyl (Avery Dennison, 3M) handles -20°F to 100°F without shrinking. Road salt does not damage vinyl — just rinse it off promptly to prevent buildup in panel gaps. Our wraps regularly last 6–7 years through Chicago winters.</p>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Is your shop climate-controlled?</h3>
<p>Yes. Our installation bay is maintained at 70°F year-round. Proper temperature is critical for vinyl adhesion — cold shops cause lifting, hot shops cause overstretching. Our climate-controlled environment ensures consistent quality regardless of the season.</p>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Do you need a permit to drive a wrapped vehicle in Chicago?</h3>
<p>No. Wrapped vehicles do not require any special permits in Chicago or Illinois. Commercial vehicle wraps are classified as advertising and are fully legal on all roads and expressways. No city sticker, sign permit, or DOT filing is required for vinyl vehicle graphics.</p>
</div>
